cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the limitations of information exchange among UAVs and ground stations, and proposes a fog-cloud computing framework to improve latency and scalability.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on the application of UAVs in large-scale mission and search operations.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a distributed fog computing architecture for UAVs.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a mathematical model to analyze distribution-based UAV topologies and fog-cloud computing framework.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of UAVs in a cooperative-based environment under the supervision of a ground station to speed up critical decision-making processes.
